      "rationale": "Validation error metrics have been computed for all five operating points. Experimental uncertainty is incorporated into the comparison. Some scatter in hemolysis index predictions at high-flow conditions suggests model-form sensitivity, but the team considers the overall agreement within engineering tolerance for the intended submission. The systematic bias observed at two operating points is attributed to rheological model limitations common to power-law hemolysis formulations."
