      "acceptanceCriteria": "Systematic model-form uncertainty quantification performed; alternative turbulence and hemolysis model forms evaluated; sensitivity of hemolysis predictions to model-form choice bounded and reported.",
      "rationale": "The k-omega SST turbulence model was selected based on prior published comparisons for rotating machinery. The power-law Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model is the industry-standard formulation used in FDA guidance. Sensitivity analyses comparing two turbulence model variants were performed at the nominal operating point and showed differences within 15% of the predicted NIH value. The assessment team considers this within acceptable engineering tolerance given the maturity of the modelling approach and the conservative safety factors applied to the clinical threshold comparison."
    },
